            "summary": "Ether's price dropped by over 4% to $2,575 on May 15, reflecting a broader decline in the cryptocurrency market where the total capitalization fell by 2.40% to $3.3 trillion. Ether's open interest decreased by 4.5% to $31.52 billion, leading to reduced trader confidence and liquidity, resulting in a decline in prices. Long positions valued at $64.6 million were liquidated compared to $21 million in short positions, contributing to a total of $312 million in liquidations across all assets. Ethereum's rally was hindered by overbought conditions, highlighted by a 71-73 RSI on the 12-hour and daily timeframes, respectively, as well as resistance levels at $2,600 and $2,800. Analysts suggest a downside target between $2,100 and $2,230 for potential entry positions. Investors are advised to conduct their own research before making investment decisions.",
